    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7642" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πί̄πτω</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πετ</span>, for <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πιπέτω</span>), ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔπῑπτον,
            πῖπτε</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεσέονται</span>,
          inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεσέεσθαι</span>, aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πέσον</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεσέειν</span>, perf. part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεπτεῶτα</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">fall;</span> fig., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐκ θῡμοῦ τινί</span>, out of one's favor, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.595</span></i>; freq. of falling in battle,
          and from the pass. sense of being killed, w. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑπό</span> (‘at the hands of’) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινος</span>, also <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑπό τινι, Ζ
            453</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 17.428</span></i>; in
          hostile sense, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">fali</span> upon, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐν
            νηυσί</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 11.311</span></i>; upon
          each other (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σύν</span>, adv.), <i><span class="en">Il. 7.256</span></i>; fig. (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐν</span>, adv.), <i><span class="en">Il. 21.385</span></i>;
          of the wind ‘falling,’ ‘abating,’ ‘subsiding,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 14.475</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            17.202</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
